                <li id="sample-newsletter-link" class="sample"><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/sample/canada-today?pgtype=subscriptionspage&version=new&contentId=CNDA&eventName=sample&module=newsletter-sign-up" target="_blank">See Sample</a></li>
                <li class="manage-email"><a href="/mem/email.html" target="_blank">Manage Email Preferences</a></li>
        <li class="logout hidden"><a href="/logout" target="_blank">Not you?</a></li>
        <li class="privacy"><a href="/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li class="contact">Opt out or <a href="/help/index.html" target="_blank">contact us</a> anytime</li>
    </ul><!-- close footer -->
    <script src="https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js" async="async" defer="defer"></script>
</div>
<div id="#continues-post-newsletter"></div>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="120" data-total-count="3956">“She told me that it was the strike that had made her mom a Quebecois,” he recalled, his face bursting into a smile.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="572" data-total-count="4528">My meeting with Mr. Nadeau-Dubois capped two days in Montreal, where I <a href="https://www.facebook.com/bilefsky/posts/10156406708338714?pnref=story">visited Martin Picard’s Cabane à Sucre Au Pied de Cochon</a> for decadent dishes including a three-layer almond foie gras cake; compiled a <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/12/reader-center/music-for-traveling-24-perfect-songs-for-my-quebec-road-trip.html?rref=collection%2Fseriescollection%2Fquebec-road-trip&amp;action=click&amp;contentCollection=reader-center&amp;region=stream&amp;module=stream_unit&amp;version=latest&amp;contentPlacement=1&amp;pgtype=collection">playlist of music</a> for my journey with songs suggested by readers; and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10156412639228714&amp;set=a.10152241651318714.1073741837.788308713&amp;type=3&amp;theater">met with Phyllis Lambert</a>, the 91-year-old architect and philanthropist. The daughter of Samuel Bronfman of the Seagram distillery empire, she, at age 27, persuaded her father to build the towering Seagram Building on Park Avenue in New York, a transformative work of 20th-century architecture.</p><figure id="media-100000005798923" class="media photo embedded layout-large-horizontal media-100000005798923 ratio-tall" data-media-action="modal" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/03/14/reader-center/quebec-lambert/quebec-lambert-master675.jpg" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" aria-label="media" role="group">
    <span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
    <div class="image">
            <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/03/14/reader-center/quebec-lambert/quebec-lambert-master675.jpg" alt="" class="media-viewer-candidate" data-mediaviewer-src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/03/14/reader-center/quebec-lambert/quebec-lambert-superJumbo.jpg" data-mediaviewer-caption="Phyllis Lambert, 91, is one of Montreal&rsquo;s most important conservationists." data-mediaviewer-credit="Jasmin Lavoie for The New York Times"  itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/03/14/reader-center/quebec-lambert/quebec-lambert-master675.jpg"/>
            <meta itemprop="height" content="503" />
            <meta itemprop="width" content="675" />
    </div>
        <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                <span class="caption-text">Phyllis Lambert, 91, is one of Montreal’s most important conservationists.</span>
                        <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder">
            <span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>
            Jasmin Lavoie for The New York Times        </span>
            </figcaption>
    </figure>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="247" data-total-count="4775">As you read this, I am on my way to Maniwaki, where I am going to reconnect with <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/16/dining/canada-indigenous-cooks.html?smid=pl-share">Cezin Nottaway</a>, a boisterous Indigenous chef. I plan to meet her on the Indigenous reserve of Kitigan Zibi, where the Algonquin tribe has been living for generations.</p><figure id="media-100000005799161" class="media photo embedded layout-large-horizontal media-100000005799161 ratio-tall" data-media-action="modal" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/01/17/dining/14quebec-nottaway/merlin_131901017_06adb369-35b8-459a-81bb-53d1fb36e3d6-master675.jpg" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" aria-label="media" role="group">
    <span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
    <div class="image">
            <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/01/17/dining/14quebec-nottaway/merlin_131901017_06adb369-35b8-459a-81bb-53d1fb36e3d6-master675.jpg" alt="" class="media-viewer-candidate" data-mediaviewer-src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/01/17/dining/14quebec-nottaway/merlin_131901017_06adb369-35b8-459a-81bb-53d1fb36e3d6-superJumbo.jpg" data-mediaviewer-caption="Cezin Nottaway at her home on the Kitigan Zibi reserve this past January." data-mediaviewer-credit="Renaud Philippe for The New York Times"  itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/01/17/dining/14quebec-nottaway/merlin_131901017_06adb369-35b8-459a-81bb-53d1fb36e3d6-master675.jpg"/>
            <meta itemprop="height" content="450" />
            <meta itemprop="width" content="675" />
    </div>
        <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                <span class="caption-text">Cezin Nottaway at her home on the Kitigan Zibi reserve this past January.</span>
                        <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder">
            <span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>
            Renaud Philippe for The New York Times        </span>
            </figcaption>
    </figure>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="258" data-total-count="5033">Ms. Nottaway is a passionate advocate for Indigenous rights, and I plan to talk to her about the anguish after the killing of Colten Boushie, a 22-year-old Indigenous man shot dead by a Saskatchewan farmer, Gerald Stanley, who was found not guilty of murder.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="167" data-total-count="5200">She and I will join my colleagues from The New York Times’s Race/Related team in a Facebook Live chat at 9 p.m. Eastern Time. Please join us at <a href="https://www.facebook.com/nytimes">facebook.com/nytimes</a>.</p><button class="button comments-button  theme-speech-bubble-large" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="140" data-total-count="5340">If you have questions for her, or ideas for places I should go to understand Quebec’s Indigenous communities, I’d love to hear from you.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="195" data-total-count="5535"><em>Follow me on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/bilefsky">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/dan_bilefsky/">Instagram</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/DanBilefsky">Twitter</a>, as well as on The Times’s <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/section/reader-center">Reader Center</a>, where I will be posting dispatches of my journey. And don’t forget to <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/canada-letter">sign up for the Canada newsletter</a>.</em></p><footer class="story-footer story-content">
    <div class="story-meta">
                        <div class="story-info"><p>Follow the Reader Center on Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/readercenter">@ReaderCenter</a>.</p>
<p><em>A note to readers who are not subscribers: This article from the Reader Center does not count toward your monthly free article limit.</em></p></div>

        
        
